[Student "S"]
{The 3\C bid shows a singleton / void in \Cs.

SOUTH doesn't have much strength above what she has already shown, but she takes advantage 
of the bidding level to make a control-showing 3\H bid.

NORTH is concerned about the \D suit with a worthless doubleton, 
and he knows that SOUTH doesn't have first-round control. He bids 4\S and SOUTH passes.}

